cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.AR, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the placement of applications in a distributed computing environment.
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of mobile edge-clouds in close proximity to users for providing real-time services.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper deals with the optimization of resource allocation in a computing system.
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with the placement of applications on physical computing systems.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also a less likely category, but possible as the paper discusses the difficulty of the application placement problem and proposes algorithms with provable performance bounds.
